00:16:18.900 --> 00:16:23.320 align:middle line:84%
And most of us do not
know which end is up.

00:16:23.320 --> 00:16:26.690 align:middle line:84%
Why is the standard
American diet killing us?

00:16:26.690 --> 00:16:32.310 align:middle line:84%
Number one-- oxidative
stress, free radicals,

00:16:32.310 --> 00:16:35.030 align:middle line:84%
which are reactive
oxygen species that

00:16:35.030 --> 00:16:38.690 align:middle line:84%
run through the body stealing
electrons and denaturing

00:16:38.690 --> 00:16:40.630 align:middle line:90%
proteins and things.

00:16:40.630 --> 00:16:44.810 align:middle line:84%
These are produced by
pesticides, herbicides.

00:16:44.810 --> 00:16:50.180 align:middle line:84%
That's important because
pesticides and herbicides

00:16:50.180 --> 00:16:51.430 align:middle line:90%
are everywhere.

00:16:51.430 --> 00:16:53.680 align:middle line:90%
And they're destroying us.

00:16:53.680 --> 00:16:57.140 align:middle line:84%
The second pillar of dietary
doom is inflammation.

00:16:57.140 --> 00:16:59.070 align:middle line:90%
You read about that everywhere.

00:16:59.070 --> 00:17:02.920 align:middle line:84%
It turns out that inflammation
is the final common pathway

00:17:02.920 --> 00:17:07.940 align:middle line:84%
in every single chronic disease,
as well as most cancers.

00:17:07.940 --> 00:17:12.119 align:middle line:84%
The third pillar of
dietary doom is glycation.

00:17:12.119 --> 00:17:14.119 align:middle line:90%
What does that mean?

00:17:14.119 --> 00:17:19.589 align:middle line:84%
And that's when that sugar
binds to proteins in the body,

00:17:19.589 --> 00:17:22.490 align:middle line:84%
and it forms a nasty
metabolic sludge

00:17:22.490 --> 00:17:24.339 align:middle line:84%
that we have no way
of getting rid of.

00:17:24.339 --> 00:17:27.130 align:middle line:84%
The fourth pillar
of dietary doom

00:17:27.130 --> 00:17:30.310 align:middle line:90%
is micronutrient insufficiency.

00:17:30.310 --> 00:17:33.660 align:middle line:84%
We don't get enough of
certain vital nutrients,

00:17:33.660 --> 00:17:38.660 align:middle line:84%
whether they're minerals like
magnesium or various vitamins.

00:17:38.660 --> 00:17:44.610 align:middle line:84%
The fifth pillar of dietary
doom is called dysbiosis.

00:17:44.610 --> 00:17:50.040 align:middle line:84%
We are a microbial ecosystem,
as we'll discuss shortly,

00:17:50.040 --> 00:17:52.730 align:middle line:84%
and if you've got
the wrong bacteria,

00:17:52.730 --> 00:17:55.390 align:middle line:84%
whether they're the ones
swimming in your eyeballs,

00:17:55.390 --> 00:17:57.674 align:middle line:84%
coating the surface
of your skin,

00:17:57.674 --> 00:18:03.687 align:middle line:84%
or residing in your digestive
tract, that can cause obesity.

00:18:03.687 --> 00:18:06.780 align:middle line:90%
It can cause mood disorders.

00:18:06.780 --> 00:18:10.490 align:middle line:84%
It can cause a variety
of different problems.

00:18:10.490 --> 00:18:13.990 align:middle line:84%
And it's the elephant in
the room of mental health

00:18:13.990 --> 00:18:15.436 align:middle line:90%
and physical health.

