Because microbes, what we
might think of as probiotics,

00:22:30.820 --> 00:22:33.830 align:middle line:90%
eat prebiotics, which are fiber.

00:22:33.830 --> 00:22:36.770 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of the problems
we have with health

00:22:36.770 --> 00:22:40.720 align:middle line:84%
have to do with we're not
feeding our microbes right.

00:22:40.720 --> 00:22:43.630 align:middle line:84%
And that leads to
problems as varied

00:22:43.630 --> 00:22:45.235 align:middle line:90%
as anxiety and depression--

00:22:45.235 --> 00:22:45.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really.

00:22:45.860 --> 00:22:47.776 align:middle line:84%
>>BORYSENKO: --mental
problems because they're

00:22:47.776 --> 00:22:49.410 align:middle line:90%
making our neurotransmitters.

00:22:49.410 --> 00:22:51.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So they're
directly related.

00:22:51.470 --> 00:22:55.300 align:middle line:84%
So most of them are toxic
in our body, actually.

00:22:55.300 --> 00:22:59.310 align:middle line:84%
We carry these toxic
chemicals in our body

00:22:59.310 --> 00:23:01.210 align:middle line:84%
that kills the
microbes in our body?

00:23:01.210 --> 00:23:04.940 align:middle line:84%
>>BORYSENKO: Well,
absolutely antibiotics.

00:23:04.940 --> 00:23:08.910 align:middle line:84%
If you think about meat that's
been raised with antibiotics,

00:23:08.910 --> 00:23:11.280 align:middle line:90%
the antibiotics get into you.

00:23:11.280 --> 00:23:14.400 align:middle line:84%
They're killing many
of the good bacteria,

00:23:14.400 --> 00:23:18.490 align:middle line:84%
and they're allowing the
overgrowth of bad bacteria.

00:23:18.490 --> 00:23:21.140 align:middle line:84%
And that's a
significant problem.

00:23:21.140 --> 00:23:24.200 align:middle line:84%
We've taken too
many antibiotics.

00:23:24.200 --> 00:23:27.180 align:middle line:84%
And right now this is a
very hot field of research

00:23:27.180 --> 00:23:30.090 align:middle line:84%
because one of the
reasons for obesity

00:23:30.090 --> 00:23:33.180 align:middle line:84%
is having the wrong
kind of gut bacteria.

00:23:33.180 --> 00:23:37.570 align:middle line:84%
You can take two
mice and feed them

00:23:37.570 --> 00:23:42.920 align:middle line:84%
in a way that causes one mice to
have a certain type of bacteria

00:23:42.920 --> 00:23:45.540 align:middle line:84%
and another mice
not to have that--

00:23:45.540 --> 00:23:48.910 align:middle line:84%
feed them the exact
same amount of calories.

00:23:48.910 --> 00:23:53.330 align:middle line:84%
One mouse will become obese,
and the other will remain lean.

00:23:53.330 --> 00:23:57.620 align:middle line:84%
So that's another part
of our obesity epidemic.

00:23:57.620 --> 00:24:00.990 align:middle line:84%
And with the PlantPlus
Diet Solution,

00:24:00.990 --> 00:24:05.030 align:middle line:84%
I would recommend that,
with very few exceptions,

00:24:05.030 --> 00:24:09.937 align:middle line:84%
you eat a pound of vegetables
a day, which sounds like a lot.

00:24:09.937 --> 00:24:11.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Do you juice them?

00:24:11.020 --> 00:24:11.847 align:middle line:90%
Do you cook them?

00:24:11.847 --> 00:24:12.680 align:middle line:90%
How do you eat them?

00:24:12.680 --> 00:24:14.510 align:middle line:84%
>>BORYSENKO: You can eat
them any way you want.

00:24:14.510 --> 00:24:16.468 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it doesn't
matter if they're juiced?

00:24:16.468 --> 00:24:18.556 align:middle line:90%


00:24:18.556 --> 00:24:21.180 align:middle line:84%
>>BORYSENKO: I mean, juicing is
lovely, but you need the fiber.

00:24:21.180 --> 00:24:22.927 align:middle line:84%
You don't want to
throw away the fiber.

00:24:22.927 --> 00:24:23.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:24:23.510 --> 00:24:24.070 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:24:24.070 --> 00:24:28.690 align:middle line:84%
>>BORYSENKO: And we do make
smoothies in the morning

00:24:28.690 --> 00:24:32.946 align:middle line:84%
with lots and lots of
vegetables and greens in them

00:24:32.946 --> 00:24:36.970 align:middle line:84%
and some fruits, maybe
apples and berries,

00:24:36.970 --> 00:24:39.010 align:middle line:84%
because both my
husband and I don't

00:24:39.010 --> 00:24:40.490 align:middle line:90%
want to eat too many carbs.

00:24:40.490 --> 00:24:43.680 align:middle line:84%
Too many, as we
know, doesn't work

00:24:43.680 --> 00:24:45.869 align:middle line:90%
for our particular metabolisms.

00:24:45.869 --> 00:24:46.910 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Very interesting.

00:24:46.910 --> 00:24:47.410 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:24:47.410 --> 00:24:50.300 align:middle line:84%
Let's take a look here at Joan
talking about the PlantPlus

00:24:50.300 --> 00:24:51.040 align:middle line:90%
Diet Solution.

00:24:51.040 --> 00:24:52.480 align:middle line:90%


00:24:52.480 --> 00:24:54.300 align:middle line:84%
>>BORYSENKO: Of course,
everybody's diet

00:24:54.300 --> 00:24:57.020 align:middle line:84%
is going to be
personalized for them.

00:24:57.020 --> 00:25:02.410 align:middle line:84%
My own diet has really
eliminated all grains.

00:25:02.410 --> 00:25:03.910 align:middle line:90%
And I'll tell you why.

00:25:03.910 --> 00:25:06.420 align:middle line:84%
I used to eat a
breakfast every morning

00:25:06.420 --> 00:25:08.920 align:middle line:90%
with oatmeal and fruits.

00:25:08.920 --> 00:25:11.880 align:middle line:84%
And an hour later, I
was absolutely starved,

00:25:11.880 --> 00:25:13.910 align:middle line:90%
and I would have to eat again.

00:25:13.910 --> 00:25:17.550 align:middle line:84%
And it turns out that
I, like many people,

00:25:17.550 --> 00:25:20.890 align:middle line:84%
do not do well eating
a diet high in carbs

00:25:20.890 --> 00:25:23.040 align:middle line:90%
because it makes me hungry.

00:25:23.040 --> 00:25:27.560 align:middle line:84%
So what do you
eat for breakfast?

00:25:27.560 --> 00:25:35.330 align:middle line:84%
I like to have either a big
shake full of delicious things,

00:25:35.330 --> 00:25:38.990 align:middle line:84%
full of berries, full
of full-fat yogurt.

00:25:38.990 --> 00:25:43.280 align:middle line:84%
There I get my probiotics,
the good bacteria

00:25:43.280 --> 00:25:48.710 align:middle line:84%
that help me stay thin and
that help my body stay healthy.

00:25:48.710 --> 00:25:51.360 align:middle line:84%
And I might mix up
a shake like that.

00:25:51.360 --> 00:25:55.680 align:middle line:84%
And then maybe I have a piece
of my fantastic almond bread.

00:25:55.680 --> 00:25:57.240 align:middle line:90%
You're going to love this.

00:25:57.240 --> 00:25:59.600 align:middle line:90%
It slices beautifully.

00:25:59.600 --> 00:26:02.290 align:middle line:84%
I can put it right
in the toaster.

00:26:02.290 --> 00:26:04.590 align:middle line:90%
And there's no flour in it.

00:26:04.590 --> 00:26:06.245 align:middle line:90%
There's hardly any carbs in it.

00:26:06.245 --> 00:26:09.125 align:middle line:84%
It's actually made of
ground almond flour.

00:26:09.125 --> 00:26:10.970 align:middle line:90%
It's totally delicious.

00:26:10.970 --> 00:26:13.040 align:middle line:84%
And I like to spice
it up with some

00:26:13.040 --> 00:26:17.950 align:middle line:84%
of the superfood spices like
cinnamon, spices like ginger.

00:26:17.950 --> 00:26:20.060 align:middle line:84%
There's a great deal
of research on them.

00:26:20.060 --> 00:26:24.060 align:middle line:84%
And these can actually
help you neurologically.

00:26:24.060 --> 00:26:28.000 align:middle line:84%
For example, these spices
that are used in India

00:26:28.000 --> 00:26:32.820 align:middle line:84%
are so important because
in Indian cooking,

00:26:32.820 --> 00:26:35.265 align:middle line:84%
you take the spices,
and you put them in oil.

00:26:35.265 --> 00:26:37.630 align:middle line:90%
It makes them bioavailable.

00:26:37.630 --> 00:26:39.920 align:middle line:84%
And there's much less
Alzheimer's disease

00:26:39.920 --> 00:26:43.540 align:middle line:90%
and dementia in India.

00:26:43.540 --> 00:26:47.430 align:middle line:84%
So for breakfast, if
I'm making an omelet,

00:26:47.430 --> 00:26:52.670 align:middle line:84%
I might put in various
curry spices, turmeric,

00:26:52.670 --> 00:26:54.940 align:middle line:90%
which has curcumin in it.

00:26:54.940 --> 00:26:58.680 align:middle line:84%
So you're going to find in
the PlantPlus Diet Solution

00:26:58.680 --> 00:27:01.050 align:middle line:90%
lots of superfoods.

00:27:01.050 --> 00:27:07.610 align:middle line:84%
So breakfast-- delicious almond
bread, maybe a boiled egg,

00:27:07.610 --> 00:27:11.340 align:middle line:84%
maybe an omelette
filled with vegetables,

00:27:11.340 --> 00:27:16.140 align:middle line:84%
maybe a big bowl of
berries, maybe a shake.

00:27:16.140 --> 00:27:18.330 align:middle line:90%
The food is really terrific.

00:27:18.330 --> 00:27:23.570 align:middle line:84%
For lunch, what I generally
eat is an enormous salad.

00:27:23.570 --> 00:27:27.710 align:middle line:84%
And by enormous, I mean not the
kind of squidgy little salad

00:27:27.710 --> 00:27:33.060 align:middle line:84%
that you'd find in a bowl
but a big plate just covered

00:27:33.060 --> 00:27:37.140 align:middle line:84%
with greens with lots
of fresh avocado in it.

00:27:37.140 --> 00:27:39.220 align:middle line:84%
My body does very
well with dairy.

00:27:39.220 --> 00:27:43.370 align:middle line:84%
So I like to chop up some feta
cheese there, then chop up

00:27:43.370 --> 00:27:48.520 align:middle line:84%
some kind of lean protein--
chicken or sometimes fish

00:27:48.520 --> 00:27:49.860 align:middle line:90%
or sardines.

00:27:49.860 --> 00:27:52.780 align:middle line:84%
It's very important
to have enough protein

00:27:52.780 --> 00:27:56.290 align:middle line:84%
because protein turns out
to be the skinny food.

00:27:56.290 --> 00:27:59.790 align:middle line:84%
And lean protein--
it actually takes

00:27:59.790 --> 00:28:04.870 align:middle line:84%
your body more calories to
incorporate it than the food

00:28:04.870 --> 00:28:05.680 align:middle line:90%
has.

00:28:05.680 --> 00:28:08.470 align:middle line:84%
So if you're trying
to lose weight,

00:28:08.470 --> 00:28:10.910 align:middle line:84%
vegetables and lean
protein is really

00:28:10.910 --> 00:28:12.780 align:middle line:90%
going to do the trick for you.

00:28:12.780 --> 00:28:14.990 align:middle line:90%
So that's oftentimes lunch.

00:28:14.990 --> 00:28:17.250 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes a fabulous salad.

00:28:17.250 --> 00:28:22.130 align:middle line:84%
And I've got some great salad
dressing recipes as well.

00:28:22.130 --> 00:28:25.172 align:middle line:84%
Because the whole third
part of the PlantPlus Diet

00:28:25.172 --> 00:28:29.830 align:middle line:90%
Solution is all recipes.

00:28:29.830 --> 00:28:33.430 align:middle line:84%
Then for dinner-- what
do we eat for dinner?

00:28:33.430 --> 00:28:35.610 align:middle line:84%
I think it's very
important not to have

00:28:35.610 --> 00:28:40.576 align:middle line:84%
to cook all the time because
most of us are just too busy.

00:28:40.576 --> 00:28:44.210 align:middle line:84%
But for dinner, I
often slow cook things.

00:28:44.210 --> 00:28:49.900 align:middle line:84%
So for example, whether you
are a vegan, a vegetarian,

00:28:49.900 --> 00:28:55.100 align:middle line:84%
or an omnivore, you can
load up your slow cooker

00:28:55.100 --> 00:28:57.590 align:middle line:84%
with a tremendous
amount of vegetables.

00:28:57.590 --> 00:29:01.755 align:middle line:84%
So your gut bacteria
just love onions.

00:29:01.755 --> 00:29:07.750 align:middle line:84%
So I like to cook with a lot
of onions and garlic and fennel

00:29:07.750 --> 00:29:13.140 align:middle line:84%
and carrots and celery and put
all these with maybe some plum

00:29:13.140 --> 00:29:16.000 align:middle line:90%
tomatoes in the slow cooker.

00:29:16.000 --> 00:29:18.370 align:middle line:84%
And then you add the
protein you want.

00:29:18.370 --> 00:29:19.710 align:middle line:90%
You can put in chicken.

00:29:19.710 --> 00:29:21.410 align:middle line:90%
You can put in lamb.

00:29:21.410 --> 00:29:25.430 align:middle line:90%
You can put in tempeh.

00:29:25.430 --> 00:29:27.880 align:middle line:90%
You can put in tofu.

00:29:27.880 --> 00:29:31.310 align:middle line:84%
You can make something so
delicious and spiced so

00:29:31.310 --> 00:29:34.720 align:middle line:84%
beautifully that any time
you go to the fridge,

00:29:34.720 --> 00:29:36.890 align:middle line:90%
it's ready to eat.

00:29:36.890 --> 00:29:39.370 align:middle line:84%
So in our house,
let me tell you,

00:29:39.370 --> 00:29:42.430 align:middle line:84%
the food has never,
ever been better.

00:29:42.430 --> 00:29:44.860 align:middle line:90%
And it's really simple.

00:29:44.860 --> 00:29:49.240 align:middle line:84%
I cook less than I ever have
before, in some ways, just

00:29:49.240 --> 00:29:52.410 align:middle line:84%
by concentrating
it-- two days a week.

00:29:52.410 --> 00:29:55.070 align:middle line:84%
And there's always
something fabulous to eat.

00:29:55.070 --> 00:29:55.780 align:middle line:90%


00:29:55.780 --> 00:29:58.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is taking
a probiotic enough

00:29:58.990 --> 00:30:01.580 align:middle line:90%
in addition to the vegetables?

00:30:01.580 --> 00:30:05.310 align:middle line:84%
Or tell me about the
probiotic concept.

00:30:05.310 --> 00:30:08.570 align:middle line:84%
>>BORYSENKO: This is a big
topic of research, for sure.

00:30:08.570 --> 00:30:10.340 align:middle line:90%
Should you take probiotics?

00:30:10.340 --> 00:30:14.820 align:middle line:84%
Because the microbiologists
don't know exactly what

00:30:14.820 --> 00:30:16.390 align:middle line:90%
the best bacteria are.

00:30:16.390 --> 00:30:18.190 align:middle line:90%
We know some of them.

00:30:18.190 --> 00:30:21.650 align:middle line:84%
And clearly, what most
of them tell you is,

00:30:21.650 --> 00:30:26.850 align:middle line:84%
eat fermented foods-- yogurt
and kefir and sauerkraut

00:30:26.850 --> 00:30:31.100 align:middle line:84%
and pickles-- but not things
that have been processed

00:30:31.100 --> 00:30:33.800 align:middle line:90%
because it kills the bacteria.

00:30:33.800 --> 00:30:37.450 align:middle line:84%
But freshly fermented
things, and that's a help.

00:30:37.450 --> 00:30:40.130 align:middle line:84%
And you can certainly
take probiotics.

00:30:40.130 --> 00:30:42.870 align:middle line:84%
It's just that you
also have to be careful

00:30:42.870 --> 00:30:45.310 align:middle line:84%
because many of the
probiotics don't

00:30:45.310 --> 00:30:47.360 align:middle line:90%
have what's advertised in them.

00:30:47.360 --> 00:30:49.962 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The cultured foods
create their own probiotic?

00:30:49.962 --> 00:30:50.670 align:middle line:90%
>>BORYSENKO: Yes.

00:30:50.670 --> 00:30:53.390 align:middle line:84%
Because what cultures
the food is the fact

00:30:53.390 --> 00:30:57.270 align:middle line:84%
that it's living bacteria
that's fermenting the food.

00:30:57.270 --> 00:30:58.620 align:middle line:90%
And that's what they do.

00:30:58.620 --> 00:31:02.450 align:middle line:84%
So you have various
bacteria-- lactobacillus

00:31:02.450 --> 00:31:05.590 align:middle line:84%
and bacteroides and
things like that that

00:31:05.590 --> 00:31:08.190 align:middle line:90%
are in those fermented foods.

00:31:08.190 --> 00:31:09.820 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, all
of this in the diet

00:31:09.820 --> 00:31:12.420 align:middle line:84%
would make you actually
feel better and allow

00:31:12.420 --> 00:31:13.850 align:middle line:90%
your brain to feel better.

00:31:13.850 --> 00:31:16.560 align:middle line:84%
And one of my favorite
books that you wrote

00:31:16.560 --> 00:31:18.550 align:middle line:84%
is the "Inner Peace
for Busy People."

00:31:18.550 --> 00:31:21.570 align:middle line:84%
And it made a difference
for me because it

00:31:21.570 --> 00:31:23.060 align:middle line:90%
changed different concepts.

00:31:23.060 --> 00:31:26.140 align:middle line:84%
But I don't think that
I could have inner peace

00:31:26.140 --> 00:31:28.980 align:middle line:90%
without the right diet.

00:31:28.980 --> 00:31:33.352 align:middle line:84%
And that's very linked to
what you talk about in there.

00:31:33.352 --> 00:31:34.060 align:middle line:90%
>>BORYSENKO: Yes.

00:31:34.060 --> 00:31:36.000 align:middle line:84%
And that's a really
good point, Lisa.

00:31:36.000 --> 00:31:39.460 align:middle line:84%
That's why my whole work has
been the mind-body connection.

00:31:39.460 --> 00:31:42.220 align:middle line:84%
And people say,
what's the diet stuff?

00:31:42.220 --> 00:31:44.080 align:middle line:90%
Where did that come from?

00:31:44.080 --> 00:31:47.820 align:middle line:84%
Because it's been like that
elephant in the living room.

00:31:47.820 --> 00:31:51.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You can't have a
healthy mind or peacefulness

00:31:51.400 --> 00:31:55.310 align:middle line:84%
or any type of inner peace
if your body is sick.

00:31:55.310 --> 00:31:56.680 align:middle line:90%
>>BORYSENKO: Exactly.

00:31:56.680 --> 00:32:00.374 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's very true,
and the inner peace-- I just

00:32:00.374 --> 00:32:01.540 align:middle line:90%
want to share this with you.

00:32:01.540 --> 00:32:04.165 align:middle line:84%
One of the things that you said
to me years and years and years

00:32:04.165 --> 00:32:07.760 align:middle line:84%
ago on my radio show is, there
is no such thing as balance.

00:32:07.760 --> 00:32:10.620 align:middle line:84%
This was when I was a
new mother and trying

00:32:10.620 --> 00:32:13.500 align:middle line:84%
to get the work-life
balance figured out.

00:32:13.500 --> 00:32:15.410 align:middle line:84%
And I said, Joan
how do I achieve

00:32:15.410 --> 00:32:18.830 align:middle line:84%
this balance, this work-life
balance and the mother thing.

00:32:18.830 --> 00:32:21.660 align:middle line:84%
You simply said, there is
no such thing as balance.

00:32:21.660 --> 00:32:22.410 align:middle line:90%
>>BORYSENKO: Yeah.

00:32:22.410 --> 00:32:26.570 align:middle line:84%
I think it's just-- it's a wrong
word because it implies that

00:32:26.570 --> 00:32:30.600 align:middle line:84%
every day, you have some of
this and a little of that

00:32:30.600 --> 00:32:32.790 align:middle line:90%
and this time and that time.

00:32:32.790 --> 00:32:35.620 align:middle line:90%
It's not so easy in our culture.

00:32:35.620 --> 00:32:40.350 align:middle line:84%
I prefer to think of balance
as almost more seasonal.

00:32:40.350 --> 00:32:44.060 align:middle line:84%
There's a time for
winter, a time for spring,

00:32:44.060 --> 00:32:45.190 align:middle line:90%
a time for summer.

00:32:45.190 --> 00:32:47.700 align:middle line:90%
Different things are happening.

00:32:47.700 --> 00:32:51.200 align:middle line:84%
But you can reduce
the seasons to a week.

00:32:51.200 --> 00:32:53.380 align:middle line:90%
You think about Sabbath.

00:32:53.380 --> 00:32:56.920 align:middle line:84%
This is a concept that's
been around for a long time.

00:32:56.920 --> 00:33:00.640 align:middle line:84%
Or the biblical thought of
letting fields lie fallow

00:33:00.640 --> 00:33:03.010 align:middle line:90%
every seventh year is a type.

00:33:03.010 --> 00:33:05.040 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't let
the field lie fallow,

00:33:05.040 --> 00:33:10.090 align:middle line:84%
the nutrients are used up,
and your crop is reduced.

00:33:10.090 --> 00:33:11.630 align:middle line:90%
And it's the same with us.

00:33:11.630 --> 00:33:16.540 align:middle line:84%
Unless we have time for being
and to lie fallow, we dry up,

00:33:16.540 --> 00:33:20.740 align:middle line:84%
and our work dries up, and we
get irritable and crotchety.

00:33:20.740 --> 00:33:23.870 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What I learned and have
learned from you over the years

00:33:23.870 --> 00:33:27.410 align:middle line:84%
is the fact that you can
have times of crazy busyness,

00:33:27.410 --> 00:33:33.602 align:middle line:84%
and that's OK as long as it's
followed by downtime, peace.

00:33:33.602 --> 00:33:34.310 align:middle line:90%
>>BORYSENKO: Yes.

00:33:34.310 --> 00:33:35.110 align:middle line:90%
You need that.

00:33:35.110 --> 00:33:38.990 align:middle line:84%
And your body fortunately
knows how to restore itself.

00:33:38.990 --> 00:33:42.110 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes we can't
do what we'd like to do.

00:33:42.110 --> 00:33:44.610 align:middle line:84%
It's great if you can
exercise every day.

00:33:44.610 --> 00:33:47.730 align:middle line:84%
It's great if you can
put aside some time

00:33:47.730 --> 00:33:50.290 align:middle line:84%
for some sort of
meditation or some way

00:33:50.290 --> 00:33:52.780 align:middle line:90%
to regulate your nervous system.

00:33:52.780 --> 00:33:54.280 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes you can't.

00:33:54.280 --> 00:33:58.990 align:middle line:84%
But the good news is if
you take regular time

00:33:58.990 --> 00:34:04.200 align:middle line:84%
and unplug yourself, your
body knows how to balance.

00:34:04.200 --> 00:34:05.630 align:middle line:90%
It restores itself.

00:34:05.630 --> 00:34:07.760 align:middle line:90%
That's called homeostasis.

00:34:07.760 --> 00:34:11.300 align:middle line:84%
But it can do that even
in our crazy busy world.

00:34:11.300 --> 00:34:13.135 align:middle line:90%
Just give it a chance.

00:34:13.135 --> 00:34:13.760 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It can.

00:34:13.760 --> 00:34:15.630 align:middle line:84%
Even if there's
chronic stress where

00:34:15.630 --> 00:34:19.357 align:middle line:84%
it feels like there's no
solution, the looping stress?

00:34:19.357 --> 00:34:20.940 align:middle line:84%
>>BORYSENKO: That's
a different thing.

00:34:20.940 --> 00:34:25.340 align:middle line:84%
Chronic looping stress leads
to a feeling of helplessness.

00:34:25.340 --> 00:34:25.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:34:25.900 --> 00:34:28.780 align:middle line:84%
>>BORYSENKO: And if you're
experiencing chronic looping

00:34:28.780 --> 00:34:31.360 align:middle line:84%
stress, you really
need to deal with it

00:34:31.360 --> 00:34:35.300 align:middle line:84%
because it might be the result,
for example, of past trauma.

00:34:35.300 --> 00:34:37.610 align:middle line:84%
And your nervous
system no longer

00:34:37.610 --> 00:34:39.460 align:middle line:90%
works the way it used to.

00:34:39.460 --> 00:34:47.230 align:middle line:84%
Very, very small stresses get
magnified in an enormous way.

00:34:47.230 --> 00:34:50.610 align:middle line:84%
And that's very important
because chronic stress really

00:34:50.610 --> 00:34:53.929 align:middle line:84%
is the underlying
basis of almost all

00:34:53.929 --> 00:34:55.940 align:middle line:84%
of our chronic
illnesses because it

00:34:55.940 --> 00:34:58.950 align:middle line:84%
leads to chronic
inflammation in the body.

00:34:58.950 --> 00:35:01.526 align:middle line:84%
So that you really
have to watch out for.

00:35:01.526 --> 00:35:03.150 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And there's
ways to resolve it,

00:35:03.150 --> 00:35:07.080 align:middle line:84%
with meditation and moments
of mindfulness so that you can

00:35:07.080 --> 00:35:07.980 align:middle line:90%
release that--

00:35:07.980 --> 00:35:10.420 align:middle line:84%
>>BORYSENKO: Well, with trauma
you really have to go back

00:35:10.420 --> 00:35:11.375 align:middle line:90%
and--

00:35:11.375 --> 00:35:12.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Deal with it.

00:35:12.250 --> 00:35:14.490 align:middle line:84%
>>BORYSENKO: There's a
lot of new work on trauma.

00:35:14.490 --> 00:35:19.470 align:middle line:84%
But it tends to work less
from thoughts to the body

00:35:19.470 --> 00:35:24.220 align:middle line:84%
and more from the somatic,
from the bodies to the thought.

00:35:24.220 --> 00:35:27.910 align:middle line:84%
But that's a very,
very important thing

00:35:27.910 --> 00:35:30.340 align:middle line:90%
is the resolution of old trauma.

00:35:30.340 --> 00:35:34.200 align:middle line:84%
And one thing I'll
say is what we

00:35:34.200 --> 00:35:38.270 align:middle line:84%
know now is if a parent
is highly traumatized,

00:35:38.270 --> 00:35:42.140 align:middle line:84%
then that can be inherited
by their offspring

00:35:42.140 --> 00:35:44.460 align:middle line:90%
for up to four generations.

00:35:44.460 --> 00:35:47.510 align:middle line:90%
This is epigenetic inheritance.

00:35:47.510 --> 00:35:50.170 align:middle line:84%
And so that was true
of me, actually.

00:35:50.170 --> 00:35:51.690 align:middle line:84%
It was one of the
reasons why I went

00:35:51.690 --> 00:35:53.780 align:middle line:84%
into the field of
mind-body medicine.

00:35:53.780 --> 00:35:58.300 align:middle line:84%
I was just stressed out all the
time, just completely a freak.

00:35:58.300 --> 00:36:00.620 align:middle line:90%
And I could not figure out why.

00:36:00.620 --> 00:36:03.510 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't like I had had
a terrible childhood.

00:36:03.510 --> 00:36:05.500 align:middle line:90%
Nothing had happened.

00:36:05.500 --> 00:36:08.260 align:middle line:84%
And then I finally
realized, oh my,

00:36:08.260 --> 00:36:11.040 align:middle line:90%
12 relatives died in Auschwitz.

00:36:11.040 --> 00:36:13.310 align:middle line:84%
My grandparents came
here because they

00:36:13.310 --> 00:36:15.840 align:middle line:90%
were fleeing from pogroms.

00:36:15.840 --> 00:36:19.250 align:middle line:84%
And the changes
that the environment

00:36:19.250 --> 00:36:22.540 align:middle line:84%
caused in their DNA--
this is new research;

00:36:22.540 --> 00:36:26.050 align:middle line:84%
it's very exciting--
have been inherited

00:36:26.050 --> 00:36:28.040 align:middle line:90%
for several generations.

00:36:28.040 --> 00:36:31.860 align:middle line:84%
And that's why I looked
like a trauma survivor.

00:36:31.860 --> 00:36:34.950 align:middle line:90%
And I had to really clear that.

00:36:34.950 --> 00:36:40.260 align:middle line:84%
And all I've learned about
meditation, breathing,

00:36:40.260 --> 00:36:44.930 align:middle line:84%
how to shift the brain has
come in response to that.

00:36:44.930 --> 00:36:48.350 align:middle line:84%
So I also want to say if
you're a trauma survivor

00:36:48.350 --> 00:36:51.500 align:middle line:84%
or if you've got
trauma in your family,

00:36:51.500 --> 00:36:55.030 align:middle line:84%
you have to look at that as a
good thing and not a bad thing

00:36:55.030 --> 00:37:01.230 align:middle line:84%
because there's that old
statement that the wounds are

00:37:01.230 --> 00:37:04.110 align:middle line:84%
where the light
comes in, that those

00:37:04.110 --> 00:37:07.790 align:middle line:84%
are what you will learn
from the very most

00:37:07.790 --> 00:37:10.300 align:middle line:84%
in really dealing
with the challenge

00:37:10.300 --> 00:37:12.217 align:middle line:90%
of having chronic stress.

00:37:12.217 --> 00:37:13.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:37:13.050 --> 00:37:17.150 align:middle line:84%
So it causes you to look to
it more and dive into it more

00:37:17.150 --> 00:37:20.510 align:middle line:84%
and realize the things that
can truly, truly help you

00:37:20.510 --> 00:37:24.460 align:middle line:84%
in your life and your
generations to come.

00:37:24.460 --> 00:37:25.020 align:middle line:90%
Amazing.

